<pb>
<p n="7">
<lb rend="indent"><q>"Good-evening, <choice><abbr type="title">Mrs.</abbr><expan>Missus</expan></choice> <persName><surname>McNab</surname></persName>," </q>she would say.</lb>
<lb>She had a pleasant way with her. The girls</lb>
<lb>all liked her. But dear, many things had changed</lb>
<lb>since then (she shut the drawer); many families</lb>
<lb>had lost their dearest. So she was dead; and</lb>
<lb><choice><abbr type="title">Mr.</abbr><expan>Mister</expan></choice><persName><surname>Andrew</surname>
</persName> killed; and <choice><abbr type="title">Dr</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice><persName><surname>Prue</surname></persName> dead too,</lb>
<lb>they said, with her first baby; but every one had</lb>
<lb>lost some one these years. Prices had gone up</lb>
<lb>shamefully, and didn't come down again neither.</lb>      
<lb>She could well remember her in her grey cloak.</lb>
</p>
